1226:Iter-054 wraps these Mathlib lemmas into the project's conventions (parameterised by $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$) so iter-055+ instantiation work for $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ can call the constructor + supremum + affine-membership directly. This mirrors iter-047's foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure (4 declarations / +60 LOC) decomposition pattern: package thin Mathlib wrappers as named project-local declarations so the substantive multi-iteration work downstream focuses purely on content (Koszul acyclicity + Čech-vs-derived comparison) rather than re-deriving infrastructure at every call site.
1268:\subsection{Existence-form producer for \texorpdfstring{$\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$}{HasAffineCechAcyclicCover} from basic-open evidence (iter-055)}
1272:Strategic value: factors out the existence-bundling step from iter-056+ substantive work, so the iter-056+ Koszul acyclicity branch and the iter-057+ Čech-vs-derived comparison branch can each prove specifically the basic-open form (which the universal Koszul + comparison arguments naturally produce), and the iter-055 producer then bundles their results into iter-053's carrier shape automatically. Mirrors the iter-053 (existence-bundled $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$) decomposition pattern: each iteration introduces one cohort of foundational scaffolding and is consumed downstream via simple call sites.
1275:[Producer for $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$ from basic-open existence, iter-055]
1276:  \label{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen}
1277:  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen}
1283:  Per affine $U$ with hypothesis $h_U : \IsAffineOpen\,U$, destructure $h\,h_U$ via $\mathtt{obtain}\,\langle s, h_s, h_{\mathrm{acyc}}, h_{\mathrm{comp}}\rangle$ to obtain a spanning subset $s$ with $h_s : \mathtt{Ideal.span}\,s = \top$ and the two class hypotheses for $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s$. Bundle into iter-053's existential cover as $\langle s, \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s, \mathtt{basicOpenCover\_supr\_of\_span\_eq\_top}\,h_U\,s\,h_s, h_{\mathrm{acyc}}, h_{\mathrm{comp}}\rangle$. The supremum hypothesis follows from iter-054's $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_supr\_of\_span\_eq\_top}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_supr_of_span_eq_top}); the two class hypotheses pass directly. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-055 pass) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end with kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
1287:[Curve specialisation, iter-055]
1288:  \label{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen_curve}
1289:  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen_curve}
1290:  \uses{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen}
1291:  Specialisation of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen} at $F := \mathtt{toModuleKSheaf}\,C$. Used by the iter-059+ packaging step.
1318:  \item \textbf{iter-059+ (packaging)}: bundle iter-056 + iter-057+ per-affine into the existence hypothesis $h$ of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen_curve}, then call $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen\_curve}\,h$ to produce the $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ instance. Iter-053 producer fires automatically.
1323:The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 closed Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$; iter-035 closed Step 3.5 (the \emph{corner-bridge}) by specialising the iter-034 universal bridge to the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ — both an abstract sheaf form (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}) and a curve specialisation (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}); iter-036 appended the immediate \emph{finrank corollary} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — landing the genus carrier $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ via $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$; iter-037 appends the parallel \emph{$\Module.\mathtt{Finite}$ transport companion} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — the algebraic counterpart of iter-036, transporting finiteness rather than finrank across the corner-bridge, via Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$. Iter-038 → iter-046 build the H⁰ Module.Finite ladder (curve specialisations + carrier predicates + Stein input + global-sections evaluation iso + producer chain end-to-end for $\IsHModuleHomFinite\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$); iter-047 lays foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure; iter-048 appends the Čech-side acyclicity carrier predicate and abstract consumer; iter-049 appends the top-supremum HModule transport (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top_curve}) — the universe $u \to u+1$ bridge that lets iter-053+ ultimately consume iter-048's $\Subsingleton$ on $\HModulePrime$ at the lattice supremum to derive the genus carrier $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ at universe $u+1$; iter-050 packages the Čech-vs-derived comparison iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso$ with $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$-based extractor (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}) and instance-driven \emph{top-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}); iter-051 appends the symmetric instance-driven \emph{intermediate-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ at universe $u$; iter-052 appends the generalised rewrite-bridge $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on an arbitrary open $U$ under the equality hypothesis; iter-053 appends the existence-bundled affine cover carrier $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HasAffineCechAcyclicCover}) and the producer $\mathtt{instance}\,\mathtt{instIsAffineHModuleVanishing\_of\_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_instIsAffineHModuleVanishing_of_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover}) — converting iter-040's $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing$ from "user-suppliable hypothesis" to "instance-synthesizable from a single carrier hypothesis", so iter-054+ needs to instantiate ONE class (the carrier) rather than three intertwined obligations; iter-054 appends foundational basic-open cover infrastructure $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover}), $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_supr\_of\_span\_eq\_top}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_supr_of_span_eq_top}), $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_isAffineOpen}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_isAffineOpen}) — wrapping Mathlib's basic-open cover lemmas into project conventions for iter-055+ to call directly; iter-055 (this iteration) appends the existence-form producer $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen}) and curve specialisation $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen\_curve}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen_curve}) — converting per-affine basic-open evidence into iter-053's existence-bundled carrier shape. The remaining work — Step 4 (the substantive Čech-vs-derived comparison theorem; iter-057+ multi-iteration; Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ but no comparison theorem; once landed as a theorem, an instance for $\HasCechToHModuleIso$ wraps it via $\langle\langle \mathtt{the\_iso}\rangle\rangle$) and Step 5 (basic-open cover acyclicity producers; iter-056 computational; Koszul-like alternating-sum complex on localisations is exact) and Step 6 (assembling the per-affine basic-open evidence and feeding it to iter-055's $\mathtt{hasAffineCechAcyclicCover\_of\_basicOpen\_curve}$, fired by iter-053's producer to give $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing$, then chained with iter-046's H⁰ ladder + iter-035/049 transport to derive the genus carrier) is iter-056+.
